<h2>The Unipept Metaproteomics Analysis Pipeline
<br><small>Bart Mesuere, Griet Debyser, Maarten Aerts, Bart Devreese, Peter Vandamme, and Peter Dawyndt</small></h2>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-9">
        <h3>Abstract</h3>
        <p>Unipept (<a href="http://unipept.ugent.be">http://unipept.ugent.be</a>) is a web application that offers a user-friendly way to explore the biodiversity of complex metaproteome samples by providing interactive visualizations. In this article, the updates and changes to Unipept since its initial release are presented. This includes the addition of interactive sunburst and treeview visualizations to the multipeptide analysis, the foundations of an application programming interface (API) and a command line interface, updated data sources, and the open-sourcing of the entire application under the MIT license.</p>

